VS001.description: Whether or not a ValueSet can be extended by users

VS002.description: A classification of a genomic variant based on its effect on a transcript or its location with respect to the transcript.

VS003.description:
The role that a variant plays in the causing a genetic condition
(see LOINC answer list https://r.details.loinc.org/AnswerList/LL4034-6.html)

VS004.description: A label applied to a sequence region

VS005.description: Value denoting whether sequence features lie on the same or different molecules

VS006.description:
Describes the existence of an allele across multiple copies of a chromosome
(Informed by LOINC answer list https://r.details.loinc.org/AnswerList/LL381-5.html but with additional codes for somatic mosaicism and asserted absence.)

VS007.description:
Classifies the transmission pattern of a condition in a pedigree.
(see LOINC Answer List https://r.details.loinc.org/AnswerList/LL3731-8.html)

VS008.description: The particular type of allele that can lead to a condition

VS010.description: Denotes whether the collected evidence is sufficient to meet a specified criteria or not

VS011.description: The functional measurement carried out in a given assay

VS012.description: Label for a group of individuals with a shared genetic background

VS013.description: The rate of missense variation in a transcript that do not lead to a genetic condition

VS014.description: The chance of having a particular genetic condition given the presence of a particular variant or damaged gene

VS015.description: The strength of association between a genetic mechanism and a condition

VS016.description: Degree of support that a set of evidence lends to a subsequent statement

VS017.description: An alteration of health status resulting from a physiopathological mechanism, and having a homogeneous clinical presentation and evolution and homogeneous therapeutic possibilities. (From MONDO)

VS018.description: The assemblage of traits or outward appearance of an individual. It is the product of interactions between genes and between genes and the environment. (From NCIT)

VS020.description: The role played by an agent in the creation of an artifact

VS021.description: The source of an allele in an individual

VS022.description: The method by which a set of people was chosen to define a group

VS023.description: The degree to which a condition implicates a specific genomic locus, such as a gene.

VS024.description: The degree to which an allele is preserved over evolutionary history

VS025.description: Whether or not parentage has been confirmed with a genetic test

VS026.description: Whether or not an individual is affected by a specific genetic condition

VS027.description: Whether or not inconsistent segretations have been observed in a pedigree

VS028.description: Denotes whether an allele leads to a non-functional transcript

VS029.description: Whether or not an allele overlaps a sequence region
